{
  "info": {
    "name": "joe-404/laravel-auth",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the joe-404/laravel-auth Laravel library.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Set the `base_url` collection variable to your app URL (e.g. `http://localhost:8000`)\n2. Register a user and run `POST /auth/login` — the collection auto-saves the token to `auth_token`\n3. Use the saved `auth_token` variable in all authenticated requests\n\n**Variables used:**\n- `base_url` — your Laravel app URL\n- `auth_token` — auto-set after login\n- `temp_token` — auto-set after register\n- `reset_token` — auto-set after magic link password reset\n- `api_token_id` — auto-set after creating an API token\n- `api_token_raw` — auto-set after creating an API token\n- `session_id` — auto-set after listing sessions",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "auth_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "temp_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reset_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "api_token_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "api_token_raw", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "session_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Registration",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Initiate Registration",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.temp_token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('temp_token', body.data.temp_token);",
                  "        console.log('temp_token saved:', body.data.temp_token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('success is true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"joe@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123!\",\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"Password123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Initiates registration. Sends OTP + magic link to the email.\n\nOn success, saves `temp_token` to collection variables (used for Reverb channel subscription).\n\n**Errors:**\n- 409 — email already registered\n- 422 — validation failed\n- 429 — rate limit exceeded"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2a. Verify OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', body.data.token);",
                  "        console.log('auth_token saved from verify-otp:', body.data.token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"joe@example.com\",\n  \"otp\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/register/verify-otp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register", "verify-otp"]
            },
            "description": "Completes registration via OTP code. Replace `123456` with the code from the email.\n\n**Errors:**\n- 422 — OTP invalid or expired"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2b. Verify Magic Link (GET from email)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', body.data.token);",
                  "        console.log('auth_token saved from verify-magic:', body.data.token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/register/verify-magic/PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL?expires=EXPIRES&signature=SIGNATURE",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register", "verify-magic", "PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "expires", "value": "EXPIRES" },
                { "key": "signature", "value": "SIGNATURE" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Copy the full magic link URL from the verification email and paste it here. The library validates the Laravel signed URL signature.\n\n**Errors:**\n- 422 — invalid or expired signature, or token already used"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Resend Verification Email",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"joe@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/email/resend-verification",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "email", "resend-verification"]
            },
            "description": "Resends OTP and/or magic link for a pending (unverified) registration. Generates a new `temp_token`, invalidating the previous Reverb subscription.\n\nAlways returns 200 regardless of whether the email exists — prevents enumeration."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Login & Logout",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', body.data.token);",
                  "        console.log('auth_token saved:', body.data.token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('success is true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              {
                "key": "X-Client-Type",
                "value": "mobile",
                "description": "Include this header to force Bearer token response in AUTH_MODE=both",
                "disabled": true
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Device-Info",
                "value": "{\"model\":\"SM-G991B\",\"platform\":\"android\",\"os_version\":\"14\"}",
                "description": "Include for mobile device session tracking",
                "disabled": true
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"joe@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticates the user. Auto-saves the Bearer token to `auth_token`.\n\n**Optional headers:**\n- `X-Client-Type: mobile` — forces Bearer token even in `AUTH_MODE=both`\n- `X-Device-Info` — JSON string for mobile device tracking\n\n**Errors:**\n- 401 — wrong credentials, or account locked out\n- 403 — account inactive or email not verified\n- 422 — validation failed\n- 429 — rate limit exceeded"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Current User (me)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Returns user profile, assigned roles, permissions, and active session count."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout (current session)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "Revokes the current session / Bearer token only."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout All Devices",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/logout/all",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "logout", "all"]
            },
            "description": "Revokes ALL sessions and tokens for this user across every device."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Password Reset",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Forgot Password (request reset)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"joe@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/password/forgot",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "password", "forgot"]
            },
            "description": "Sends OTP and/or magic link for password reset. Always returns 200 to prevent email enumeration."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2a. Reset via OTP (one step)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"joe@example.com\",\n  \"otp\": \"654321\",\n  \"password\": \"NewPassword123!\",\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"NewPassword123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/password/reset/otp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "password", "reset", "otp"]
            },
            "description": "Resets password in one step using the OTP from the email. All existing sessions are revoked on success.\n\n**Errors:**\n- 422 — OTP invalid, expired, or user not found"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2b. Validate Magic Link (get reset_token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.reset_token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('reset_token', body.data.reset_token);",
                  "        console.log('reset_token saved:', body.data.reset_token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/password/reset/magic/PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL?expires=EXPIRES&signature=SIGNATURE",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "password", "reset", "magic", "PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "expires", "value": "EXPIRES" },
                { "key": "signature", "value": "SIGNATURE" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Paste the full URL from the password reset email. Validates the signature and returns a short-lived `reset_token` UUID (valid 15 minutes).\n\nAuto-saves `reset_token` to collection variables."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2c. Confirm Reset (with reset_token)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reset_token\": \"{{reset_token}}\",\n  \"password\": \"NewPassword123!\",\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"NewPassword123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/password/reset/confirm",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "password", "reset", "confirm"]
            },
            "description": "Submits the new password using the `reset_token` received from the magic link step. All sessions are revoked on success.\n\n**Errors:**\n- 422 — reset_token invalid or expired (older than 15 minutes)"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Password Change",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Change Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"current_password\": \"Password123!\",\n  \"new_password\": \"NewPassword456!\",\n  \"new_password_confirmation\": \"NewPassword456!\",\n  \"logout_all\": false\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/password/change",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "password", "change"]
            },
            "description": "Changes the authenticated user's password.\n\n**`logout_all`:** When `true`, all other sessions and tokens are revoked but the current session remains active.\n\n**Errors:**\n- 422 — current_password incorrect, new password same as current, or validation failed"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Sessions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Active Sessions",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const sessions = body.data && body.data.sessions;",
                  "    if (sessions && sessions.length > 0) {",
                  "        const nonCurrent = sessions.find(s => !s.is_current);",
                  "        if (nonCurrent) {",
                  "            pm.collectionVariables.set('session_id', nonCurrent.id);",
                  "            console.log('session_id saved (non-current):', nonCurrent.id);",
                  "        }",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/sessions",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "sessions"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all active sessions for the authenticated user with device info, IP, geo location, and last-active timestamp. Auto-saves a non-current `session_id` for use in the delete request."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke Specific Session",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/sessions/{{session_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "sessions", "{{session_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Revokes the session with the given ID. Also deletes the associated Sanctum token if the session was API-based."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "API Tokens",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List My API Tokens",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/api-tokens",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "api-tokens"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all API tokens owned by the authenticated user.\n\n**Requires:** `AUTH_MODE` must be `api` or `both`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create API Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data) {",
                  "        if (body.data.raw_token) {",
                  "            pm.collectionVariables.set('api_token_raw', body.data.raw_token);",
                  "            console.log('api_token_raw saved:', body.data.raw_token);",
                  "        }",
                  "        if (body.data.token && body.data.token.id) {",
                  "            pm.collectionVariables.set('api_token_id', body.data.token.id);",
                  "            console.log('api_token_id saved:', body.data.token.id);",
                  "        }",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"CI Pipeline\",\n  \"abilities\": [\"read\", \"deploy\"],\n  \"expires_in_days\": 365\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/api-tokens",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "api-tokens"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new API token. The `raw_token` in the response is shown **only once** — store it securely.\n\n**Fields:**\n- `abilities`: array of permission strings. Use `[\"*\"]` for full access.\n- `expires_in_days`: `null` = never expires, max 3650.\n\n**Token format:** `auth_at_{base64}`\n\nAuto-saves `api_token_raw` and `api_token_id`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke API Token",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/api-tokens/{{api_token_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "api-tokens", "{{api_token_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Revokes the API token with the given ID. Only the owner can revoke their own tokens (admin endpoints available separately)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Use API Token on a Protected Route",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{api_token_raw}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/your-protected-route",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["your-protected-route"]
            },
            "description": "Example of calling a route protected by `auth.api-token` middleware. Replace `/your-protected-route` with your actual endpoint.\n\nThe middleware validates that:\n1. The token starts with `auth_at_`\n2. The SHA-256 hash matches a stored record\n3. The token is active and not expired\n4. The token has the required abilities"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Google OAuth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Google Redirect URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.redirect_url) {",
                  "        console.log('Open this URL in a browser:', body.data.redirect_url);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/social/google/redirect",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "social", "google", "redirect"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the Google OAuth authorization URL. Open `data.redirect_url` in a browser to start the OAuth flow.\n\n**Requires:** `AUTH_GOOGLE_ENABLED=true`\n\n**Errors:**\n- 403 — Google OAuth is disabled"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Google OAuth Callback",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', body.data.token);",
                  "        console.log('auth_token saved from Google OAuth:', body.data.token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/social/google/callback?code=GOOGLE_AUTH_CODE&state=STATE",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "social", "google", "callback"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "code", "value": "GOOGLE_AUTH_CODE", "description": "Auth code from Google redirect" },
                { "key": "state", "value": "STATE", "description": "State parameter from Google redirect" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Google redirects here after authorization. In practice, the user's browser is redirected here automatically — you would not call this directly from Postman.\n\n**Three cases handled automatically:**\n1. Provider ID matches → existing user logged in\n2. Email matches → Google account linked to existing user, then logged in\n3. Brand new → user created (email pre-verified), role assigned, then logged in\n\n**Errors:**\n- 403 — Google OAuth disabled, or account inactive\n- 400 — OAuth exchange failed"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Admin — API Tokens",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Admin: List All API Tokens",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/admin/api-tokens",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "admin", "api-tokens"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all API tokens across all users.\n\n**Requires:** `super-admin` or `admin` role."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Admin: Create Unowned API Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.raw_token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('api_token_raw', body.data.raw_token);",
                  "        console.log('admin api_token_raw saved:', body.data.raw_token);",
                  "    }",
                  "    if (body.data && body.data.token && body.data.token.id) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('api_token_id', body.data.token.id);",
                  "    }",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Service Account Token\",\n  \"abilities\": [\"*\"],\n  \"expires_in_days\": null\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/admin/api-tokens",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "admin", "api-tokens"]
            },
            "description": "Creates an API token not attached to any user. Useful for service accounts.\n\n**Requires:** `super-admin` or `admin` role."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Admin: Update API Token",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"abilities\": [\"read\"],\n  \"expires_in_days\": 30\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/admin/api-tokens/{{api_token_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "admin", "api-tokens", "{{api_token_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Updates the abilities and/or expiry of any API token.\n\n**Fields (all optional):**\n- `abilities` — replaces the current abilities array\n- `expires_in_days` — `null` clears expiry (never expires)\n\n**Requires:** `super-admin` or `admin` role."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Admin: Revoke Any API Token",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/admin/api-tokens/{{api_token_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "admin", "api-tokens", "{{api_token_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Revokes any API token regardless of owner.\n\n**Requires:** `super-admin` or `admin` role."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Health Checks & Reference",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Response — Success Example",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Reference: every successful response has this shape:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Human readable message.\",\n  \"data\": { }\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Response — Error Example (wrong password)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"joe@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"wrong\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Reference: every error response has this shape:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"message\": \"Human readable error.\",\n  \"errors\": { }\n}\n```\n\nHTTP status codes used:\n- 200 OK\n- 201 Created\n- 400 Bad Request\n- 401 Unauthorized\n- 403 Forbidden\n- 404 Not Found\n- 409 Conflict\n- 422 Unprocessable Entity\n- 423 Locked (account lockout)\n- 429 Too Many Requests"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
